<subSubSection id="538FDCB3FFF1FF9EFF0200CBFB5E5247" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFF1FF9EFF0200CBFE8350BE" blockId="20.[212,1172,481,640]" box="[212,344,481,505]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">
<heading id="40623854FFF1FF9EFF0200CBFE8350BE" box="[212,344,481,505]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" reason="5">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFF1FF9EFF0200CBFE8350BE" box="[212,344,481,505]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFF1FF9EFF020322FE8153C7" blockId="20.[212,1172,481,640]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">
Native to coastal waters of 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFF1FF9EFDDF0323FDAF5367" box="[521,628,520,544]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">East Asia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFD550322FC5D5367" author="Geiger DL &amp; Owen B" box="[643,902,520,544]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" refId="ref10588" refString="Geiger DL, Owen B. 2012. Abalone: worldwide Haliotidae. Hackenheim: ConchBooks." type="book" year="2012">Geiger and Owen 2012</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFF1FF9EFC6B0322FC235367" box="[957,1016,520,544]" name="Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Chile</collectingCountry>
this species is commercially harvested, with aquaculture farms in Caldera (
<geoCoordinate id="7EA1E9FFFFF1FF9EFC450302FC085307" box="[915,979,552,576]" degrees="27" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" precision="55555" value="-27.0">27° S</geoCoordinate>
), northern 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFF1FF9EFB8E0302FB485307" box="[1112,1171,552,576]" name="Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Chile</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFF0D0362FE465327" author="Valdovinos C" box="[219,413,584,608]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="111 - 164" refId="ref14097" refString="Valdovinos C. 1999. Biodiversidad de moluscos chilenos: base de datos taxonomica y distribucional. Gayana. 63: 111 - 164." type="journal article" year="1999">Valdovinos 1999</bibRefCitation>
). It was first introduced to the country in 1982 (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFC3B0362FE9153C7" author="Flores-Aguilar RA &amp; Gutierrez A &amp; Ellwanger A &amp; Searcy-Bernal R" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="705 - 711" refId="ref10484" refString="Flores-Aguilar RA, Gutierrez A, Ellwanger A, Searcy-Bernal R. 2007. Development and current status of abalone aquaculture in Chile. J Shellfish Res. 26: 705 - 711." type="journal article" year="2007">Flores-Aguilar et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFF1FF9EFF0203EBFD71539E" blockId="20.[212,1157,705,768]" box="[212,682,705,729]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">
<heading id="40623854FFF1FF9EFF0203EBFD71539E" box="[212,682,705,729]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" reason="5">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFF1FF9EFF0203EBFD71539E" box="[212,682,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Possible mechanism of introduction/Status</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFF1FF9EFF0203C2FB5E5247" blockId="20.[212,1157,705,768]" box="[212,1157,744,768]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">
Imported to 
<collectingCountry id="6382CFA8FFF1FF9EFEB003C2FE7A5247" box="[358,417,744,768]" name="Chile" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Chile</collectingCountry>
for aquaculture (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFDBF03C2FC9B5247" author="Castilla JC &amp; Uribe M &amp; Bahamonde N &amp; Clarke M &amp; Desqueyroux-Faundez R &amp; Kong I &amp; Moyano H &amp; Rozbaczylo N &amp; Santelices B &amp; Valdovinos C &amp; Zavala P" box="[617,832,744,768]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="213 - 232" refId="ref9326" refString="Castilla JC, Uribe M, Bahamonde N, Clarke M, Desqueyroux-Faundez R, Kong I, Moyano H, Rozbaczylo N, Santelices B, Valdovinos C, Zavala P. 2005. Down under the southeastern Pacific: marine non-indigenous species in Chile. Biol Invasions. 7: 213 - 232." type="journal article" year="2005">Castilla et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFC8603C2FBAE5247" author="Flores-Aguilar RA &amp; Gutierrez A &amp; Ellwanger A &amp; Searcy-Bernal R" box="[848,1141,744,768]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="705 - 711" refId="ref10484" refString="Flores-Aguilar RA, Gutierrez A, Ellwanger A, Searcy-Bernal R. 2007. Development and current status of abalone aquaculture in Chile. J Shellfish Res. 26: 705 - 711." type="journal article" year="2007">Flores-Aguilar et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="538FDCB3FFF1FF9EFF02026BFE065567" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFF1FF9EFF02026BFEED521E" blockId="20.[212,1172,833,1056]" box="[212,310,833,857]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">
<heading id="40623854FFF1FF9EFF02026BFEED521E" box="[212,310,833,857]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" reason="5">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFF1FF9EFF02026BFEED521E" box="[212,310,833,857]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B2A8F38FFF1FF9EFF020243FE065567" blockId="20.[212,1172,833,1056]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">
Herbivorous species, this species has an indirect impact on the communities of the native rocky kelp 
<taxonomicName id="DC95F4BBFFF1FF9EFE7C02A0FD5D52E6" box="[426,646,906,929]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Lessonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nigrescens">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFF1FF9EFE7C02A0FD5D52E6" box="[426,646,906,929]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Lessonia nigrescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DC95F4BBFFF1FF9EFD1102A0FC7452E6" box="[711,943,905,929]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Lessonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="trabeculata">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFF1FF9EFD1102A0FC7452E6" box="[711,943,905,929]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Lessonia trabeculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are used as abalone food in Chilean aquaculture facilities (
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFD2A0283FC005286" author="Castilla JC &amp; Uribe M &amp; Bahamonde N &amp; Clarke M &amp; Desqueyroux-Faundez R &amp; Kong I &amp; Moyano H &amp; Rozbaczylo N &amp; Santelices B &amp; Valdovinos C &amp; Zavala P" box="[764,987,937,961]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="213 - 232" refId="ref9326" refString="Castilla JC, Uribe M, Bahamonde N, Clarke M, Desqueyroux-Faundez R, Kong I, Moyano H, Rozbaczylo N, Santelices B, Valdovinos C, Zavala P. 2005. Down under the southeastern Pacific: marine non-indigenous species in Chile. Biol Invasions. 7: 213 - 232." type="journal article" year="2005">Castilla et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFC380283FE9352A7" author="Flores-Aguilar RA &amp; Gutierrez A &amp; Ellwanger A &amp; Searcy-Bernal R" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="705 - 711" refId="ref10484" refString="Flores-Aguilar RA, Gutierrez A, Ellwanger A, Searcy-Bernal R. 2007. Development and current status of abalone aquaculture in Chile. J Shellfish Res. 26: 705 - 711." type="journal article" year="2007">Flores-Aguilar et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
). This species is also a primary introduction vector for the non-indigenous boring polychaete species 
<taxonomicName id="DC95F4BBFFF1FF9EFDD002C3FC6E5547" authority="Sato-Okoshi, 1998" authorityName="Sato-Okoshi" authorityYear="1998" box="[518,949,1000,1025]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis id="29E1532AFFF1FF9EFDD002C3FD0E5547" box="[518,725,1001,1025]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751">Polydora uncinata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFD3602C2FC6E5547" author="Sato-Okoshi W" box="[736,949,1000,1024]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="277 - 288" refId="ref13522" refString="Sato-Okoshi W. 1998. Three new species of polydorids (Polychaeta, Spionidae) from Japan. Species Divers. 3: 277 - 288." type="journal article" year="1998">Sato-Okoshi, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7F04F2C9FFF1FF9EFC1E02C2FEB45567" author="Radashevsky VI &amp; Olivares C" pageId="20" pageNumber="1751" pagination="489 - 496" refId="ref13153" refString="Radashevsky VI, Olivares C. 2005. Polydora uncinata (Polychaeta: Spionidae) in Chile: an accidental transportation across the Pacific. Biol Invasions. 7: 489 - 496." type="journal article" year="2005">Radashevsky and Olivares 2005</bibRefCitation>
). UA, II.
</paragraph>
